social_posts.post_text: 🥂 Here’s to 2023 with the Apicellas

I’ve had a lot of homes… 

 Hudson’s Mill has been my home for two years. It’s been the place where I spend 75% of my waking hours, the place where I made friends in my new town after moving 350 miles, the place I invite my friends and family, the place that embraced me and trusted me and allowed me to do my proverbial “thing”, the place that made me laugh and sing and dance, the place that won awards proving “we are the best”. 

I am so grateful, because without my immediate connection with @jimguarasci , I might still be wandering around NY and NJ looking for a “home”. 

Any hospitality worker knows that if you can’t find peace, satisfaction, and friendship in your workplace - you won’t be happy. 60 or 70 hours a week you’re surrounded by your coworkers with no reprieve, it’s important that those relationships are ones that you value. It can be incredibly toxic, or incredibly supportive.. (sometimes it’s both) 
I’ve been searching for this feeling of ownership and connection since I left my very first kitchen job, and I am so fortunate to have  found it when, and where I did. 

In the new year I’ll be taking a different path; as the corporate culinary director for CB5 hospitality consulting. 

It makes me sad to leave day-to-day restaurant kitchen life, I’ll miss the chaos and the fun and the daily inevitable “ahhhhhhh!”…. But, I’m excited for this next step, and what it will bring for me and my future in this very special, exhausting, and exceptionally gratifying industry that, for better or worse, I love. 

🥂 2023

I had the BEST impromptu visit with @jimguarasci this afternoon, what started as a “quick lunch” turned into a four course meal because everything that came out of the kitchen looked so incredible! I never document my restaurant trips this way but I seriously couldn’t help myself. 

Highlights from @millelucipizza 👇 

1.) BRING A FRIEND OR A CROWD - solo dining here is not for the faint of heart! I ordered a salad, focaccia, a pizza, and a cannoli and because everything is served family style I have a TON of amazing leftovers that’ll feed me for the next few days. (Reserve a spot for a large party and order a 5+ ft pizza for a game of thrones level dining experience 🥲) 
2.) I ordered the Diavolo pizza and in my head was thinking “I wish I could ask for hot honey with this, but it’s my first time here and I don’t want to alter anything” AND THE PIZZA CAME OUT WITH MF HOT HONEY, an adorable little jar on the side no less. 
3.) Do NOT sleep on these cannolis, I was up walking around checking the place out and got back to my table and said “holy cannoli” aloud.. for the first time in my life, ever. I was full already from several carb-heavy courses but I still couldn’t help but dig into that bad boy absolutely shamelessly, like I was going to the electric chair. 
4.) The most beautiful cappuccino I’ve ever had in my life, ever. Jimmy offered a splash of Sambuca at the table, I declined today (I had two glasses of amazing wine I forget the name of, also recommended by Jimmy)- but how special is that table-side service? 

All in all 10’s across the board, check ‘em out and support small business in Rockland County! Jimmy taught me everything he knows and if you want to see the OG pro at work bring the homies to @millelucipizza @millelucipizza  @millelucipizza

October, really? 

I’m busy, but I’ve still got the sauce. 

I accidentally made three hot sauces that are perfectly colored like a stoplight, twirled cotton candy, played with dry ice, written hundreds of recipes, worked with dozens of chefs and cooks and in a wild twist learned how to design kitchens with CAD? Not sure where that fits in, but somehow i’m out here literally conjuring up dining concepts, writing menus and opening boutique restaurants for a living. 

Watching the new Hell’s Kitchen season and reflecting makes me really think about what 5 years can change. It’s a lot, #goredteam as always ♥️❤️

((By the way, all of those cocktails are fake, the sangria is literally a giant glass of pickled onion juice))
